==English==
===Pronunciation===
'sēn-yûr
===Etymology===
< Old French ''seignor,'' or ''seignior'' < Latin ''senior''
===Noun===
#a. a feudal lord; nobleman who held his lands by feudal grant.<p>b. any lord (holder) of a manor; gentleman. 
#a title of respect, formerly corresponding (especially in France) approximately to ''Sir''.
